claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: A table presenting vaccine effectiveness (VE) percentages (with 95% confidence intervals) for different influenza vaccines (recombinant quadrivalent influenza vaccine RIV4, standard-dose quadrivalent influenza vaccine SD-IIV4, RIV4 combined with high-dose quadrivalent influenza vaccine HD-IIV4 and adjuvanted influenza vaccine Adj-IV), stratified by age groups (18–64 years and ≥65 years). The table contains only VE data and does not include any information on hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content per strain, so it does not support the claim. Note: Image only shows vaccine effectiveness metrics; no antigen dosage details are present.
